<section class="hero">
  <h1>Lump Sum or <em>Ladder In?</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-subtitle">Lump sum or DCA &mdash; and does where you sit in the channel change the answer?</div>
  <p class="subtitle">Not about timing, not about temperament &mdash; about valuation relative to the Power Law channel. Decisive when cheap, patient when stretched, committed always.</p>
</section>

<main class="content-area">

  {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

  <div class="section-intro lsl-prose">
    <p>Every exchange has a dollar-cost-averaging calculator. Run honestly against a rising asset, they all reach the same flat conclusion &mdash; <em>you should have lump-summed</em> &mdash; which is true, unsatisfying, and undifferentiated.</p>
    <p>This page asks the better question. The lump-sum-versus-ladder decision isn&rsquo;t really about <em>timing</em> and isn&rsquo;t really about <em>temperament</em> &mdash; it&rsquo;s about <strong>valuation relative to the Power Law trajectory</strong>. Low in the channel, spreading purchases just means paying more as price reverts up toward trend, so deploy decisively. Stretched into the upper channel, spreading is the model-rational hedge against the mean-reversion the channel itself predicts. Mid-channel is a genuine coin-flip. And underneath all of it: over a long enough horizon, <em>every</em> entry &mdash; even the literal worst tops in Bitcoin&rsquo;s history &mdash; recovers to a large multiple. The tactic is a margin; commitment is the foundation.</p>
  </div>

