      <p class="lsl-chart-caption lsl-cap-retro">How the all-now-vs-ladder edge changes across the channel. Below the line, deploying all at once accumulated more BTC (amber); above it, laddering did (blue). The settled &ldquo;lump-sum usually wins&rdquo; debate flips on its axis once you condition on valuation.</p>
      <p class="lsl-chart-caption lsl-cap-proj">Anchored at today, under the three forward paths the channel permits &mdash; revert to trend, ride the floor, stretch then revert (excursions sized to <em>recent</em> amplitude, never 2013&rsquo;s). The lesson holds prospectively too: starting low, deploying wins under essentially every path; high up, laddering wins under the revert paths. It&rsquo;s robustness across permitted paths &mdash; never a single forecast. The faint dashed line is the retrospective curve, for the two-lens agreement.</p>
