        <p><strong>The forward read carries more humility than the backtest.</strong> Today&rsquo;s floor is knowable; today&rsquo;s position relative to a <em>future</em> trend is less so.</p>
        <p><strong>The math models a holder who never capitulates.</strong> If deploying a lump and watching it fall would push you to sell and leave entirely, laddering is staying-power insurance &mdash; a small tactical cost for a steadiness the backtest can&rsquo;t see. It&rsquo;s the one honest reason to ladder even when the channel says deploy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

